            "guid": "P-t3p6IO)=",
            "note_model_uuid": "5fcbb45c-6a48-11f1-b3c2-1e4652aeb480",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "fields": [
                "<code>OrganizationAccountAccessRole</code>",
                "The <code>OrganizationAccountAccessRole</code> is a preconfigured AWS IAM role automatically created in member accounts when using AWS Organizations. It grants administrative privileges (via the <code>AdministratorAccess</code> policy) to the management account, allowing organization administrators to manage, troubleshoot, and configure sub-accounts."
            ],
            "guid": "q4Z({$t/Qe",
            "note_model_uuid": "5fcbb45c-6a48-11f1-b3c2-1e4652aeb480",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "fields": [
                "RCP",
                "Resource Control Policy"
